              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Normandie Universite, Unicaen, 14032 Caen,",
                "France"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "LINAC"
                ],
                "institute": "1USAMSU"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Experiment performed at the ReA3",
                "accelerator facility at Michigan State University"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Radioactive beams of K and Ar ions were produced by",
                "colliding 48Ca beams at 140A MeV with a Be production",
                "target at the coupled-cyclotron facility at MSU-NSCL.",
                "The resulting reaction products were filtered by the",
                "A1900 spectrometer and thermalized in a gas stopper.",
                "They were subsequently extracted from the gas stopper,",
                "charge bred to a high-charge state, and accelerated",
                "by the ReA3 linac. The intensities of the K and Ar",
                "beams incident on the target ranged between 1.0E+4",
                " (44Ar/s) and 4.5E+4 (39K/s)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The 16-O target was produced by evaporating 28Si in a",
                "vacuum of 1E-6 Torr. The oxygen content in the target",
                "was measured by Rutherford backscattering. Oxygen",
                "thickness was of 98+-4 mu-g/cm2 along with a Si",
                "thickness of 258+-10 mu-g/cm2."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES",
                "IOCH",
                "MCPLT"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two microchannel plate detectors",
                "with two axial field ionization detectors were placed",
                "upstream of the target to identify incoming ions by",
                "dE-TOF method. The electron emission foil of the",
                "downstream MCP detector also served as the target in",
                "the experiment"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Evaporation residue were detected in an annular",
                "Si detectors that subtend the angular range 1.0 deg <",
                "Theta(lab) < 7.3 deg."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MCPLT"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two microchannel plate detectors were placed",
                "downstream of the target to measure time of flight of",
                "heavy reaction products."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EDE",
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Particles were identified using dE-TOF method"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The fusion cross section sigmaF is extracted from the",
                "measured yield of ERs through the relation sigmaF =",
                "NER/(epsilonER *t*NI ), where NI is the number of",
                "beam particles of a given type incident on the target,",
                "t is the target thickness, epsilonER is the detection",
                "efficiency, and NER is the number of evaporation",
                "residues detected. The number NI is determined by",
                "counting the particles with the appropriate time of",
                "flight between the two MCPs that have the correct",
                "identification in the E-TOF map. The measured target",
                "thickness was used. The number of detected residues,",
                "NER, is determined by summing the number of detected",
                "residues identified by the ETOF technique.",
                "Uncertainty in identifying an ER associated with",
                "fusion on 16O is reflected in the error bars",
                "presented. To obtain the detection efficiency,",
                "epsilonER, a statistical model was used to describe",
                "the deexcitation of the fusion product together with",
                "the geometric acceptance of the experimental setup.",
                "The detection efficiency varied between ~82% and 83%",
                "over the entire energy range."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-T",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The statistical uncertainties of the",
                "measurement dominate the error bars shown."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-1",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The second-largest contribution to the total",
                "uncertainty in the cross section is due to the target",
                "thickness and is 4%."
              ]
            }
          ],
